{"nodes": [{"id": "specs_2026_06_10_settings_window_design", "label": "Settings Window Design Spec", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "docs/superpowers/specs/2026-06-10-settings-window-design.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "specs_2026_06_10_settings_window_design_settingswindow", "label": "SettingsWindow Two-Pane Native Window", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "docs/superpowers/specs/2026-06-10-settings-window-design.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Two-pane sidebar in a dedicated native window chosen over a roomier modal or full-screen route; seven panes, every pane backs a real feature (Notifications included only after verifying usePipelineNotifications is a real source). Each pane is a focused unit reading its config slice and saving via one RPC; panes do not know about each other. No cross-window reactive state \u2014 each window does its own RPC."}, {"id": "specs_2026_06_10_settings_window_design_agentaccesspane", "label": "Agent Access (MCP) Pane", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "docs/superpowers/specs/2026-06-10-settings-window-design.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Makes the MCP server fully usable from the UI (enable/port/token reveal/copy/regenerate, client-config snippet, live status) \u2014 no more hand-editing config.json. The bearer token is returned only by explicit reveal/regenerate RPCs, never in getConfig/getMcpStatus. Disconnect also stops the MCP server, folding in the deferred clearConfig \u2192 stopMcp fix."}, {"id": "specs_2026_06_10_settings_window_design_opensettingswindow", "label": "openSettingsWindow Singleton Opener", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "docs/superpowers/specs/2026-06-10-settings-window-design.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Module-level singleton ref (like issueWindows but single): a second open focuses the existing window instead of spawning another; the \u2318, menu item and lumen:open-settings event both route here, retiring the modal."}], "edges": [{"source": "specs_2026_06_10_settings_window_design", "target": "specs_2026_06_10_settings_window_design_settingswindow", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "docs/superpowers/specs/2026-06-10-settings-window-design.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "specs_2026_06_10_settings_window_design", "target": "specs_2026_06_10_settings_window_design_agentaccesspane", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "docs/superpowers/specs/2026-06-10-settings-window-design.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "specs_2026_06_10_settings_window_design", "target": "specs_2026_06_10_settings_window_design_opensettingswindow", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "docs/superpowers/specs/2026-06-10-settings-window-design.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "specs_2026_06_10_settings_window_design_settingswindow", "target": "specs_2026_06_10_settings_window_design_agentaccesspane", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "docs/superpowers/specs/2026-06-10-settings-window-design.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "specs_2026_06_10_settings_window_design_opensettingswindow", "target": "specs_2026_06_10_settings_window_design_settingswindow", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "docs/superpowers/specs/2026-06-10-settings-window-design.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "specs_2026_06_10_settings_window_design",